        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 28 at 4:57PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 457 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Coleman, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Coleman, Santa Anna, Valera, Trickham, Echo, Fisk, and Hords Creek
Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
west central Texas.</instruction>
